<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,548,899]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,656,683]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Leaf mine.</emphasis>
A long, yellowish, interparenchymal mine, with the frass deposited in a single large lump. Up to three larvae may feed in a common mine (
<bibRefCitation author="Spencer, K. A. &amp; Steyskal, G. C." box="[623,911,693,719]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="1 - 478" refId="ref19712" refString="Spencer, K. A. &amp; Steyskal, G. C. (1986) Manual of the Agromyzidae (Diptera) of the United States. USDA Agricultural Research Service Agriculture Handbook, 638, 1 - 478. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 119606" type="journal article" year="1986">Spencer &amp; Steyskal 1986</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ellis, W. N." box="[923,1042,693,719]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refId="ref18901" refString="Ellis, W. N. (2018) Leafminers and plant galls of Europe. Available from: http: // www. bladmineerders. nl (accessed 20 August 2018)" type="url" year="2018">Ellis 2018</bibRefCitation>
). M. Palmer (
<emphasis box="[1195,1262,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">in litt.</emphasis>
) noted that one of the adults exited through a hole 
<quantity box="[541,596,729,755]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="cm" value="1.0">1 cm</quantity>
away from its puparium.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,548,899]" box="[199,1229,764,791]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,764,791]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Puparium.</emphasis>
Slender, brown; formed within the mine (
<bibRefCitation author="Spencer, K. A. &amp; Steyskal, G. C." box="[797,1086,765,791]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="1 - 478" refId="ref19712" refString="Spencer, K. A. &amp; Steyskal, G. C. (1986) Manual of the Agromyzidae (Diptera) of the United States. USDA Agricultural Research Service Agriculture Handbook, 638, 1 - 478. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 119606" type="journal article" year="1986">Spencer &amp; Steyskal 1986</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ellis, W. N." box="[1098,1217,765,791]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refId="ref18901" refString="Ellis, W. N. (2018) Leafminers and plant galls of Europe. Available from: http: // www. bladmineerders. nl (accessed 20 August 2018)" type="url" year="2018">Ellis 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
